parameters: Gosh, where the heck is that book..?
Wow... Look at all this stuff!
It’s like Lovecraft’s garage in here.
If Lovecraft was a hoarder and a slob, maybe.
But you’re right, there are some neat items in here.
Damn, if I had my CoK notebook, I could
write down some quest ideas for the campaign!
<I swear all she thinks about is CoK...>
WELCOME! Finding everything you desire, darlings?
We were mostly just browsing, hoping to-
Hold that thought, I just remembered I need
to let my husband out of the iron maiden.
... You put your husband in an iron maiden..?
I know, I spoil him too much. Greggy!
It’s been two hours, and we have customers!
Yes, NOW! You can tinker with your new toy later.
Damn, I almost got out that time!
Of course you did, dear. I promise we can play later.
Ohohoho! Will we now, my love?
The things I’m going to do to you...
Heavens me! Where are our manners? Welcome to Hex-Rated!
I’m Gregory P. Draven, owner of this fine emporium
of the eerie. I see you’ve met my wife, Valerie.
What can we do for the cute couple today? Shrunken heads?
Medieval devices for that added spice in your life?
No kidding, that’s how my Aunt and Uncle met! I’ll give
you a deal on some slightly used caskets. Interested?
ACTUALLY... We were hoping to see Sabrina.
I’m \N[001] and this is my sister, Ashley.
Greggy, we have to get the polaroid camera for this!
Brina, where did you run off to, darling??
You two must really be something to have Sabrina
invite you over. Though I can’t imagine why it took
this long to meet her friends. Cigar?
I actually haven't met her to be honest.
My brother said she could help us with a... School project.
Any friends of our little monster are friends of mine!
Between you and me, she’s been in a sour mood lately.
Maybe you two can help with that.
Brina! Come now, your sweet little friends have
come to see you! And you were supposed to be
T-The hell, guys!? You said you’d be gone all evening
checking out antiques in the next town over!
We will be, soon, but there’s no rush. Greggy was just
checking the new inventory. Good thing he was too, because
otherwise we wouldn’t have met your darling classmates!
*Whispering* He seems cute, confirmed single, and I
think he’s packing a monster downstairs...
You better snatch him off the market fast, Brina.
I hate to cut this party short but my love
and I are due for an appointment. Got a seller
offering cursed puzzle boxes. Wild, huh?
Yes, please go. NOW. I’ll watch
the store like I always do.
It was very nice meeting you!
You kids behave yourselves! Or don’t, if you
plan on having some real fun while we’re gone!
Brina, don’t forget to finish stocking
the shelves before hanging out with-
YES! OKAY! I’LL DO IT, JUST GO!
And just who the fuck are you?
MY NAME is Ashley, \N[001]’s sister, and I don’t
appreciate your tone. I’m here to make sure you’re
legit, and don’t put him in further danger.
Ashley is helping me with my... Problem,
and WE are hoping you could too.
Before we get down to business, I need to finish
tending to the store. Once that’s done, we can
discuss what the other knows about black magic.
Then MAYBE... We can help each other out.
Perfect, we’d be happy to pitch in.
\N[001], take a box, find a shelf, stock it. Doesn’t matter
which, we don’t exactly have an organized system here.
I’ll be here if you have questions.
And what do you want me to do?
You can go over there by the bookshelf and find me a copy
of “Demonic Do’s and Don’ts Volume 5”. We'll need that
later once we dive in. Do you think you can handle that?
I’d be delighted to go and do that, FAR AWAY over there...
I’ll just get started on this...
Here it is. Hey there, Pins!
You watching the store while Sabrina is out?
<You know, he’s actually kind of cute.
In a creepy sort of way... >
I swear to god if you’re actually fucking haunted...
AH! Such a big dick... Fucking... Huge... FUCK ME!!!
<Guess my cock stats really got her worked up!>
If she sees me, I’m dead... >
<But not before I document this wonderful display first.
I mean she is thinking about me after all.
Alright, enough screwing around. Time to hit Cup a Feel for
some ritual candles. Wonder who Sabrina’s seller is?
Take the box and stock the shelves,
Hey, these masks are kind of awesome. What are they for?
Those? Gregory bought a collection of Japanese oni masks.
They’re said to ward off evil spirits.
Ha... Yeah, I suppose it is...
I know what these are, tarot cards!
They’re supposedly able to tell your future.
From my experience it’s a load of shit. But they’re still
fun to fool around with. Maybe...
Maybe I could show you how to read them sometime.
So I wanted to ask you something...
The doll, “Pins” I believe you called him? You seemed
pretty upset when he went missing. Mind if I ask why?
It’s... Stupid to say out loud...
That’s okay. I’m kind of an idiot if you hadn’t noticed.
Just wait until you hear what I sold my soul for.
<... Aw fuck it, he did find him for me after all. >
I... My life has kind of been a shitshow, especially when I
was little. When I was six years old, I made Pins to wish
bad things happen to people who let me down...
I never really expected it to work, he was
more of a coping tool. But as time went on
he became my good luck charm, my best friend.
He was always there when I was scared or alone...
No, I think it’s pretty normal actually.
Having a fucked up patchwork doll you created
to hurt people with is normal to you?
What I mean is... I don’t know your history, and it’s
probably none of my business anyway.
But if you’ve lost people or things that mean something
to you, it’s only natural to hang on to what little you
<The fuck is up with this guy? More
<Alright. Let’s have some fun with him... >
Well that’s how I see it, even if it sounds
a bit corny. What do youaaah..?
<HA! Knew the perv would get hot and
bothered over a little playful teasing. >
be envious of a plush toy... >
Y-Yeah! Just about! I see you’re
keeping a close eye on Pins.
Hmm? Oh! Well... I wouldn’t want to
lose the little guy again, right?
Do you think this is a good place
GAH! I’m so sorry! I dropped a vial of... Something!
*Giggle* Relax, dude. That’s the cheap shit anyway.
Are you sure it was in that section?
Oh that thing? Made it up.
Made it-WHY?! Why would you make me
look for a book that doesn’t exist!
Listen, “Edgar Allen’s Hoe”, we don’t have time for games!
My brother is in danger, and I’m not afraid to kick your
pale ass up and down this goddamn Halloween supply store to
get the answers to save him! Do you understand me, bitch?!
Hahaha! Damn, Ashley. I think I’m starting to like you!
Let’s talk shop! See this book?
What? I took a Latin course. It’s great for my RPGs.
ANYWAY... Yes, your sister's correct. The Pages of Pain is
said to be the documented incantations of a mad scribe who
tried communicating with the other side, and I have a copy.
Sure as hell wasn’t easy to obtain,
I can tell you that right now.
So we know it works, that much is clear. But what I
want to know is why you even have it in the first place.
What were you trying to achieve, Sabrina?
I have my reasons. Now, I showed you mine,
so it’s only fair that you show me yours...
W-What, like r-right now? Kinda weird with my sister here,
but then again she’s already seen it so-
N-Not that you fucking perv! What is wrong with you?!
*Sigh*... It’s part of his demonic contract.
I sold my soul to a succubus for a giant
dick and the power over people’s wills.
... So how big are we talking here?
What?! I want to know what \N[001]
I hardly see what’s- wait, NINETEEN inches?
How the heck do you even know that?
Well of course I measured it!
<Though you don’t need to know the exact details... >
It doesn’t have runes or tiny horns on it, does it?
No, it’s perfectly normal! Size aside I mean.
My turn to ask a question: why didn’t my demonic persuasion
work on you back at school?
Your girl did her homework before that botched summoning.
I’ve managed to ward myself against a good bit of demon
A witch has to be fully prepared before
she starts bargaining with a hellspawn.
Right, because you were SO prepared the
first time and almost got my brother killed.
Hey! This thing is written in at least three dead languages
by a nutcase with poor handwriting. I think I did pretty
damn good for a first try.
Anything in there that says how to break a contract?
Nope, not from what I’ve translated thus far.
But I may have an idea...
This mean son of a bitch is called “Orgoluuk The Collector”.
He’s old enough, powerful enough, and has a reputation of
Your big plan is to summon another, more dangerous demon?!
It won’t be like last time. We’ll have safeguards in place,
and a specific demon to channel, which were two things I
was sorely lacking during the first attempt.
So you want to summon an archdemon, trap it in one place,
then blackmail it to give us what we want in exchange for
Look at that, a big dick AND a big brain too!
Correct, Devil Boy. Orgoluuk can break your contract,
I get everything my little black heart desires,
And what precautions do we need in place
to pull this off without disaster?
Just three key things from what I can tell. We’ll need
special ritual candles made from a rare beeswax, essence of
the damned, and blessed holy water - to fortify the trap.
I’m willing to at least give
it a try, Ash. What do you say?
Bitchin! Fortunately for us, I have a lead to our first
item on the shopping list. Give this note to the owner of
Cup A Feel, the coffee shop on West Central.
She’s my connection for a lot of
Sounds easy enough. Holy water shouldn’t be too hard
either, so we can save that for last. But how the heck are
we supposed to get “essence of the damned”?
I can look into that, along with possible plan B’s that are
less suicidal. I’m sure there’s lore I can dig up online
that can point us in the right direction.
And while you two do that, I’ll continue my research
with The Pages of Pain. Let’s go people, chop chop!
Well look who it is! Back again?
I was afraid Brina might have scared you off.
Hi Mrs. Draven! Don’t worry, I’m starting to get used to
her... Quirks. Just dropping by to give her something.
D’aww! Brina Baby is lucky to have someone like you.
She’s a sweet, kind, and sensitive girl...
<Are we still talking about the same Sabrina? >
Uh... She’s one of a kind, that’s for sure. Is she around?
Upstairs in her room, locked in like every evening.
You know I can’t express how delighted I am that you two
That poor girl has been through enough
Really? I mean, I didn’t want to pry,
but I felt something was up.
Oh darling you don’t even know half the story! A father
that ran off when she was a newborn, a mother who abandoned
her into perpetual foster care not long after that...
It’s no wonder she’s had such a terrible
time connecting with people ever since.
Wow I... I had no idea... She didn’t say anything.
*Sigh* I wouldn’t expect her to, I shouldn’t even be telling
you this. Gregory and I have taken in a lot of unwanted
treasures over the years, and Brina is our most cherished.
I just want her to be happy, it’s all I’ve ever wanted
for that sweet little girl since she was twelve.
Just know that I will do ANYTHING to protect her. Can I
count on you to do the same, \N[001]? I think you’ll find
me most appreciative for making my Brina Baby happy.
S-Sure thing, Mrs. D. I’ll do my best.
Good. Because if you don’t, I’ll show you
what happened to my last three husbands...
Oh cobwebs! I have to go dig him up!
You... Buried him? Like in the ground?
Darling it’s just how we play. You’ll understand when
you’re married. Now don’t let me keep you from Brina,
I have to get the shovel.
Oh and one more thing, Darling...
<Ah who am I to judge? I’ve seen weirder things since my
deal was made. Let’s see what Sabrina is up to upstairs. >
... Well of course no one NEEDS a Brazen Bull, but think
of our basement. It would go perfect in the south corner!
I told you no more tools of torture
until we finish painting down there!
Aaah! There he is! And he brought a gift too!
Here to raise a little hell with our monster, sport?
Hopefully something a bit more relaxing
this time if I’m being completely honest.
Oh Greggy, please, go fetch Brina for him!
Darling, I can’t even begin to describe my gratitude for
you. Gregory and I haven’t felt this close to our little
Brina in... Well, ever in fact!
Aw, it’s really nothing Mrs. Draven.
Sabrina just had to figure out some things, you know?
But I’m glad you guys are closer.
We could get really close too...
Mister Draven and I have a wonderful, healthy,
OPEN marriage... If you get my meaning.
Perhaps one of these days I could join you and Brina for a
little fun. You’re practically one of the family now...
And it really is best to keep things in the family, no?
Here already? I must have lost
track of time. You ready to go?
you have a place in mind?
Damn right I do! See you guys later!

You watching the store while Sabrina is out?
